    "commerce.order_status_changed": {
      "post": {
        "tags": [
          "commerce"
        ],
        "operationId": "commerce.order_status_changed",
        "requestBody": {
          "description": "# commerce.order_status_changed\nThe **Order Status Changed** event is triggered whenever an order\u2019s status is updated in Zoom Commerce (for example, when an order is placed, processed, or canceled).\n\n## Prerequisites\n\nTo receive this event, ensure the following configurations are in place for your [Marketplace app](https://marketplace.zoom.us/user/build).\n\n* **Event Subscriptions** are enabled.\n* A valid **Event Notification Endpoint URL** is specified.\n* The **Order status changed** event subscription is enabled under the **commerce** event category.\n\n**[Scopes](https://developers.zoom.us/docs/integrations/oauth-scopes-overview/):** `zoom_commerce:read:admin`\n\n**[Granular Scopes](https://developers.zoom.us/docs/integrations/oauth-scopes-overview/):** `zoom_commerce:read:order:admin`\n\n**Event type**: `commerce.order_status_changed`\n",
          "content": {
            "application/json": {
              "schema": {
                "type": "object",
                "properties": {
                  "event": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "description": "The name of the event."
                  },
                  "event_ts": {
                    "type": "integer",
                    "format": "int64",
                    "description": "The timestamp at which the event occurred."
                  },
                  "event_id": {
                    "type": "string",
